{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fa39a030-d72d-4246-9c3d-0d0b45710b1b","content":"In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove this line entirely: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**That's it.** Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is the **default** runner. Setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was opting *out* of it. By removing that property, you opt back in.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n- **CLI**: Run tests with `dotnet test` as usual, but the output format changes slightly.\n- **Filters**: Use `--filter` the same way, but some advanced filter syntax may differ.\n- **Extensions**: If you used VSTest adapters/extensions, check for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., coverage, loggers).\n- **CI**: If your CI parses `.trx` files, add `<TestingExtensionsProfile>Default</TestingExtensionsProfile>` or pass `--report-trx` to keep generating them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fd1d1869-112f-4d9c-9706-fd6937fb65a4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in an MSTest.Sdk project. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing configuration - I don't need to explore any codebase for this.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":392,"requestId":"CFE0:1FFE72:62A5479:6DD30E1:69EC0EC7"},"id":"1b4f9b0a-e486-4238-8adb-dbeffdf509a2","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:10.136Z","parentId":"87e61776-8c37-429c-9b18-3a4b926fbcbe"}
